(207, 'grading_system', 'What is the grading and GPA system at PMAS-Arid Agriculture University?', '📊 **PMAS-Arid Agriculture University - Grading & GPA System:**\r\n\r\n**Grading Scale:**\r\n\r\n🅰️ **A (Excellent):** 85-100 marks → 4.00 GPA\r\n🅱️ **B+ (Very Good):** 80-84 marks → 3.50 GPA\r\n🅱️ **B (Good):** 75-79 marks → 3.00 GPA\r\n🆎 **B- (Above Average):** 71-74 marks → 2.50 GPA\r\n🅲️ **C+ (Average):** 68-70 marks → 2.25 GPA\r\n🅲️ **C (Satisfactory):** 64-67 marks → 2.00 GPA\r\n🅲️ **C- (Below Average):** 60-63 marks → 1.75 GPA\r\n🅳️ **D (Marginal Pass):** 50-59 marks → 1.00 GPA\r\n❌ **F (Fail):** Below 50 marks → 0.00 GPA\r\n\r\n**GPA Calculation Formula:**\r\n\r\n📐 **GPA (Semester):**\r\nGPA = Σ(Grade Points × Credit Hours) ÷ Total Credit Hours\r\n\r\n📐 **CGPA (Cumulative):**\r\nCGPA = Total Grade Points Earned ÷ Total Credit Hours Attempted\r\n\r\n**Example Calculation:**\r\n\r\n**Semester Courses:**\r\n- Math (3 CH): Grade B (3.00) → 3 × 3.00 = 9.00\r\n- English (3 CH): Grade A (4.00) → 3 × 4.00 = 12.00\r\n- Physics (4 CH): Grade B+ (3.50) → 4 × 3.50 = 14.00\r\n- Lab (1 CH): Grade A (4.00) → 1 × 4.00 = 4.00\r\n\r\n**Total:** 39.00 points ÷ 11 credit hours = **3.54 GPA** ✅\r\n\r\n**Credit Hours System:**\r\n\r\n📚 **Theory Course:** Usually 3 credit hours\r\n🔬 **Lab/Practical:** Usually 1 credit hour\r\n📖 **Combined:** Theory + Lab = 4 credit hours total\r\n\r\n**Credit Hour Formula:**\r\n- 1 Credit Hour = 1 hour lecture/week (16 weeks)\r\n- Lab Credit = Usually half of theory credit\r\n\r\n**Grade Classifications:**\r\n\r\n🏆 **Excellent:** CGPA 3.50 - 4.00\r\n⭐ **Good:** CGPA 3.00 - 3.49\r\n👍 **Satisfactory:** CGPA 2.50 - 2.99\r\n⚠️ **Average:** CGPA 2.00 - 2.49\r\n❌ **Probation:** CGPA below 2.00\r\n\r\n**Academic Standing:**\r\n\r\n✅ **Good Standing:** CGPA ≥ 2.00\r\n⚠️ **Academic Warning:** CGPA < 2.00 (first semester)\r\n🚨 **Academic Probation:** CGPA < 2.00 (second consecutive semester)\r\n❌ **Dismissal:** CGPA < 2.00 (third consecutive semester)\r\n\r\n**Degree Requirements:**\r\n\r\n🎓 **Graduation Requirement:**\r\n- Minimum CGPA: 2.00\r\n- Complete all credit hours\r\n- No \"F\" grades in core courses\r\n- Clear all dues\r\n\r\n🏅 **Honors/Distinctions:**\r\n- **High Distinction:** CGPA ≥ 3.75\r\n- **Distinction:** CGPA 3.50 - 3.74\r\n- **Merit:** CGPA 3.00 - 3.49\r\n\r\n**Grade Improvement:**\r\n\r\n🔄 **Repeat Course:**\r\n- Can repeat failed courses (F grade)\r\n- Can repeat passed courses for better grade\r\n- Only latest grade counts in CGPA\r\n- Previous attempt shows on transcript\r\n\r\n📝 **Incomplete Grade (I):**\r\n- Given for valid reasons\r\n- Must complete within next semester\r\n- Converts to F if not completed\r\n\r\n**Withdrawal Policy:**\r\n\r\n🚪 **W (Withdrawal):**\r\n- Withdraw before deadline\r\n- Does not affect CGPA\r\n- Shows on transcript\r\n- Fee not refunded\r\n\r\n**Important Notes:**\r\n\r\n⚠️ **Rounding:** GPA/CGPA rounded to 2 decimal places\r\n📊 **Transcript:** All attempts shown, latest grade used\r\n🎯 **Scholarship:** Minimum 3.00 CGPA usually required\r\n💡 **Improvement:** Focus on high credit hour courses for bigger impact\r\n\r\n**How to Check Your GPA/CGPA:**\r\n\r\n📱 **Student Portal:**\r\n- Login to student portal\r\n- View semester-wise GPA\r\n- Check cumulative CGPA\r\n- Download transcript\r\n\r\n👨‍🏫 **Department Office:**\r\n- Request unofficial transcript\r\n- Check academic standing\r\n- Verify credit hours completed\r\n\r\n📧 **Controller of Examinations:**\r\n- For official transcript\r\n- For verification letters\r\n- For grade disputes\r\n\r\n**Pro Tips for Better GPA:**\r\n\r\n💡 **High-Credit Courses:** Excel in 3-4 CH courses (bigger impact)\r\n💡 **Don\'t Skip:** Complete all courses, don\'t withdraw unnecessarily\r\n💡 **Repeat Strategically:** Repeat only if you can get A/B\r\n💡 **Plan Ahead:** Take challenging courses with lighter semester load\r\n💡 **Track Progress:** Calculate your CGPA regularly to stay on target\r\n\r\n📞 **Questions?** Contact Controller of Examinations Office\r\n\r\n🎯 Aim for 3.00+ CGPA for better opportunities!', 'Academic', 'All', 1, 'static', '2026-02-11 15:32:03', '2026-02-11 15:32:03', NULL, 'Complete PMAS-Arid grading and GPA system with calculations and examples'),
(208, 'exam_policies', 'What are the exam policies and rules?', '📋 **PMAS-Arid Exam Policies & Rules:**\r\n\r\n**Before Exam:**\r\n✅ 75% attendance mandatory to sit for exams\r\n📝 Admit card/ID required for entry\r\n🆔 No entry without valid university ID\r\n⏰ Arrive 15 minutes before exam starts\r\n\r\n**During Exam:**\r\n📱 **Strictly Prohibited:**\r\n   • Mobile phones/smart watches\r\n   • Books, notes, cheat sheets\r\n   • Electronic devices\r\n   • Communication with others\r\n   • Looking at others\' papers\r\n\r\n✅ **Allowed:**\r\n   • Transparent water bottle\r\n   • Scientific calculator (if specified)\r\n   • Stationery items\r\n   • Admit card & ID\r\n\r\n**Exam Conduct:**\r\n🚫 No talking during exam\r\n✋ Raise hand for questions/issues\r\n📝 Write only in answer booklet\r\n⏰ Cannot leave in first 30 minutes\r\n🚪 Cannot re-enter after leaving\r\n\r\n**Answer Sheet Rules:**\r\n✍️ Write roll number clearly\r\n📄 Use only blue/black pen\r\n❌ No pencil (except diagrams)\r\n📝 Don\'t tear pages from booklet\r\n✅ Sign attendance sheet\r\n\r\n**Cheating/Unfair Means:**\r\n⚠️ **Penalties:**\r\n   • Exam cancellation\r\n   • Course failure (F grade)\r\n   • Suspension (1-2 semesters)\r\n   • Expulsion (severe cases)\r\n\r\n**Late Arrival:**\r\n⏰ Up to 30 min: Entry allowed\r\n⏰ After 30 min: Not allowed\r\n❌ No extra time given\r\n\r\n**Medical Emergency:**\r\n🏥 Inform invigilator immediately\r\n📝 Medical certificate required\r\n📋 Can apply for makeup exam\r\n\r\n**Result Queries:**\r\n📊 Results announced via portal\r\n📝 Rechecking: Within 7 days\r\n💰 Rechecking fee applies\r\n⏰ Decision within 2 weeks\r\n\r\n📞 **Contact:** Controller of Examinations\r\n\r\n🎯 Follow rules for fair examination!', 'Academic', 'All', 1, 'static', '2026-02-11 15:44:32', '2026-02-11 15:44:32', NULL, 'Complete exam policies for PMAS-Arid'),
(209, 'credit_hours_system', 'What is the credit hours system?', '📚 **PMAS-Arid Credit Hours System:**\r\n\r\n**What is a Credit Hour?**\r\n📖 1 Credit Hour = 1 hour of lecture per week for 16 weeks\r\n🔬 Lab/Practical = 2-3 hours per week for 1 credit hour\r\n\r\n**Typical Course Structure:**\r\n\r\n**Theory Courses:**\r\n📝 3 Credit Hours = 3 lectures/week (48 hours/semester)\r\n📚 Examples: Math, English, Chemistry\r\n\r\n**Lab/Practical:**\r\n🔬 1 Credit Hour = 3 hours lab/week\r\n🧪 Examples: Physics Lab, Computer Lab\r\n\r\n**Combined Courses:**\r\n📖 Theory (3 CH) + Lab (1 CH) = 4 Total Credit Hours\r\nExample: Computer Programming (3+1)\r\n\r\n**Semester Load:**\r\n\r\n**Minimum:** 12 credit hours (full-time student)\r\n**Normal:** 15-18 credit hours per semester\r\n**Maximum:** 21 credit hours (with permission)\r\n**Summer:** Maximum 9 credit hours\r\n\r\n**Degree Requirements:**\r\n\r\n🎓 **BS Programs:** 130-136 credit hours (4 years)\r\n   • Core courses: 90-100 CH\r\n   • Electives: 20-30 CH\r\n   • University requirements: 10-16 CH\r\n\r\n📊 **Breakdown by Year:**\r\n   • Year 1: 30-34 CH\r\n   • Year 2: 30-34 CH  \r\n   • Year 3: 30-34 CH\r\n   • Year 4: 30-34 CH\r\n\r\n**Course Types:**\r\n\r\n**Compulsory/Core:** Must take (e.g., Major subjects)\r\n**Electives:** Choose from options\r\n**University Requirements:** English, Pak Studies, Islamiat\r\n\r\n**Credit Hour Impact on GPA:**\r\n\r\n💡 **Higher credit hours = More impact on CGPA**\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n- 4 CH course with A (4.0) = 16 grade points\r\n- 1 CH course with A (4.0) = 4 grade points\r\n\r\n**Pre-requisites:**\r\n⚠️ Some courses require completion of other courses first\r\n📋 Check course catalog for requirements\r\n\r\n**Repeat Policy:**\r\n🔄 Can repeat failed courses\r\n📊 Latest grade counts toward CGPA\r\n💰 Must pay course fee again\r\n\r\n**Withdrawal:**\r\n🚪 Can drop course before deadline\r\n📝 \"W\" appears on transcript\r\n⚠️ Doesn\'t affect CGPA but counts toward total attempts\r\n\r\n**Transfer Credits:**\r\n🔄 Can transfer from other HEC-recognized universities\r\n📋 Maximum: Usually 30% of degree requirements\r\n✅ Approval from department required\r\n\r\n📞 **Contact:** Academic Advisor or Department Office\r\n\r\n🎯 Plan your credit hours wisely each semester!', 'Academic', 'All', 1, 'static', '2026-02-11 15:44:41', '2026-02-11 15:44:41', NULL, 'Credit hours system explanation for PMAS-Arid'),
(210, 'how_to_apply_admission', 'How to apply for admission?', '📝 **PMAS-Arid Admission Application Process:**\r\n\r\n**Step-by-Step Guide:**\r\n\r\n**1️⃣ Check Eligibility:**\r\n✅ Check program requirements\r\n📊 Verify minimum marks/CGPA\r\n📅 Confirm you meet criteria\r\n\r\n**2️⃣ Get Admission Form:**\r\n\r\n**Online:**\r\n🌐 Visit: www.uaar.edu.pk/admissions\r\n💳 Pay challan fee (PKR 1,000-2,000)\r\n🏦 Pay at designated bank\r\n📱 Get online form access\r\n\r\n**Offline:**\r\n🏢 Visit Admissions Office\r\n💰 Purchase prospectus + form\r\n📋 Collect from sales counter\r\n\r\n**3️⃣ Fill Application Form:**\r\n✍️ Fill all sections carefully\r\n📄 Provide accurate information\r\n🆔 Attach required documents\r\n📸 Paste recent photographs\r\n\r\n**4️⃣ Required Documents:**\r\n\r\n📋 **Checklist:**\r\n✅ Matric/O-Level certificates & marksheets\r\n✅ FSc/A-Level certificates & marksheets (attested)\r\n✅ CNIC copy (student + parents)\r\n✅ Domicile certificate\r\n✅ Character certificate\r\n✅ Migration certificate (if from other board)\r\n✅ Passport size photos (4-6)\r\n✅ Hafiz-e-Quran certificate (if applicable)\r\n\r\n**5️⃣ Submit Application:**\r\n\r\n**Online Submission:**\r\n📱 Upload scanned documents\r\n💾 Save application reference number\r\n📧 Confirmation email received\r\n\r\n**Physical Submission:**\r\n🏢 Submit at Admissions Office\r\n📅 Before deadline\r\n🧾 Get receipt/acknowledgment\r\n\r\n**6️⃣ Pay Test Fee:**\r\n💰 Entry test fee: PKR 1,500-3,000\r\n🏦 Pay at designated bank\r\n📄 Keep receipt safe\r\n\r\n**7️⃣ Download Admit Card:**\r\n📅 Available 3-5 days before test\r\n🌐 Login to admission portal\r\n🖨️ Print admit card\r\n✅ Verify details\r\n\r\n**8️⃣ Appear for Entry Test:**\r\n📍 Check test venue on admit card\r\n⏰ Arrive 30 minutes early\r\n🆔 Bring admit card + CNIC\r\n✏️ Bring pencil, eraser, sharpener\r\n\r\n**9️⃣ Check Merit List:**\r\n📊 Published online after 1-2 weeks\r\n🌐 Check admission portal\r\n📱 SMS notification (if registered)\r\n📋 Also displayed at campus\r\n\r\n**🔟 If Selected - Complete Enrollment:**\r\n\r\n**Documents to Submit:**\r\n📄 Original certificates (for verification)\r\n💰 Paid fee challans\r\n📋 Admission form (signed)\r\n🏥 Medical fitness certificate\r\n📸 Additional photographs\r\n\r\n**Fee Payment:**\r\n💵 Admission fee + 1st semester fee\r\n🏦 Pay at designated banks\r\n📅 Within deadline (usually 7 days)\r\n\r\n**Final Steps:**\r\n✅ Collect student ID card\r\n📚 Get course registration\r\n📋 Attend orientation\r\n🎓 Classes begin!\r\n\r\n**Important Deadlines:**\r\n\r\n📅 **Fall Semester:**\r\n- Advertisement: June-July\r\n- Application deadline: Late July\r\n- Entry test: Early August  \r\n- Merit list: Mid August\r\n- Classes start: September\r\n\r\n📅 **Spring Semester:**\r\n- Advertisement: December\r\n- Application deadline: Late January\r\n- Entry test: Early February\r\n- Merit list: Mid February  \r\n- Classes start: Late February\r\n\r\n**Important Tips:**\r\n\r\n💡 Apply early - don\'t wait for deadline\r\n💡 Double-check all documents\r\n💡 Keep copies of everything\r\n💡 Save all fee receipts\r\n💡 Check portal regularly for updates\r\n💡 Prepare well for entry test\r\n💡 Have backup program choices\r\n\r\n**Test Preparation:**\r\n📚 Covers: English, Math, Subject knowledge\r\n📖 Past papers available online\r\n⏰ Duration: Usually 2-3 hours\r\n📊 MCQ format\r\n\r\n**For Queries:**\r\n📞 Admissions Office: +92-51-9290160\r\n📧 Email: admissions@uaar.edu.pk\r\n🌐 Website: www.uaar.edu.pk\r\n💬 Visit campus for guidance\r\n\r\n🎯 Start your PMAS-Arid journey today!', 'Admissions', 'All', 1, 'static', '2026-02-11 15:45:40', '2026-02-11 15:45:40', NULL, 'Complete admission application process for PMAS-Arid');
